Reasoning: The paper deals with the performance analysis of cell center and edge users in a random two-tier network, which involves the study of interference statistics, spectrum allocation techniques, and spatial randomness in the location of base stations and cellular traffic. These topics are closely related to the fields of networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
